msgid "Koma Bayanina"
msgstr "ኮማ ባያኒና\n\n\nPlease note: \"Koma\" seems to be a proper noun ( likely a name), and \"Bayanina\" seems to be a noun or an adjective. Without more context, it's difficult to provide a more accurate translation. If you provide more context or information about the words, I can try to give a more precise translation. \n\nHowever, assuming \"Koma\" is a name and \"Bayanina\" is an adjective, the translation could be:\n\n\n ኮማ (Koma) - ኮማ\nባያኒና (Bayanina) - ባያኒና ( possibly meaning \"my Bayanina\" or \"of Bayanina\")\n\n\nThe translation \"ኮማ ባያኒና\" is a direct transcription of the given phrase, but the actual translation may vary depending on the context in which it is used."

